'''Vimpulse''' extends [ViperMode Viper] with Vim features like Visual mode and text objects.

: '''Latest release: [[vimpulse.el|Vimpulse 0.3.1]]''' (always on !EmacsWiki)

If you want bleeding edge, you can check out the [http://my-svn.assembla.com/svn/vimpulse/trunk/ current SVN revision].

== Installation ==

Place ##vimpulse.el## in your ##site-lisp## directory (or anywhere in your ##load-path##). Then add the following line to ##.emacs##:

    (require 'vimpulse)

If you want linear undo/redo, download and install [http://wonderworks.com/download/redo.el redo.el] (included with XEmacs).

Vimpulse automatically enables [ViperMode Viper]. You can temporarily disable Viper (and Vimpulse) with `C-z'.

== News ==

* Emacs-compatible Visual selection (normal, line and block).
* New movement keys: `C-o', `C-i', `C-w hjkl', `gb', `gd', `N%', `+', `_'.
* Modal keybinding functions: `vimpulse-map', `vimpulse-imap' and `vimpulse-vmap'.
* Improved text objects support.

== Feedback ==

Feel free to edit this page with bug reports, suggestions and improvements. You can also [https://www.assembla.com/user/signup sign up] with our [http://my-trac.assembla.com/vimpulse/report/1 bug tracker] and create a ticket there.

